#4.5--> Give error bar if y_error = [0.12, 0.13, 0.2, 0.1]
# error data
y_error = [0.12, 0.13, 0.2, 0.1]

#x-axis
plt.xlim(0.5,4.5)
plt.xticks([1,2,3,4])


#Y-axes
plt.ylim(19.8,21.2)
plt.yticks([20, 21, 20.5, 20.8])
#plot
plt.plot(X,y,color="m",linestyle="--",linewidth=5,marker="o",markersize=10)
# plot error bar
plt.errorbar(X,y,yerr=y_error,color="r",linestyle="None",marker="None")

#title
plt.title("Simple plot",color="c",fontsize=30)
# labels
plt.xlabel("X axis",color="g",fontsize=30)
plt.ylabel("Y axis",color="b",fontsize=30)

#4.9-->
"""
Create a dataframe from following data
'first_name': ['Jason', 'Molly', 'Tina', 'Jake', 'Amy'],

'last_name': ['Miller', 'Jacobson', 'Ali', 'Milner', 'Cooze'],

'female': [0, 1, 1, 0, 1],

'age': [42, 52, 36, 24, 73],

'preTestScore': [4, 24, 31, 2, 3],

'postTestScore': [25, 94, 57, 62, 70]
Draw a Scatterplot of preTestScore and postTestScore, with the size of each point determined by age
"""
dct={"first_name":['Jason', 'Molly', 'Tina', 'Jake', 'Amy'],
    'last_name': ['Miller', 'Jacobson', 'Ali', 'Milner', 'Cooze'],
    'female': [0, 1, 1, 0, 1],
    'age': [42, 52, 36, 24, 73],
     'preTestScore': [4, 24, 31, 2, 3],
     'postTestScore': [25, 94, 57, 62, 70]}
# creat DataFrame
df=pd.DataFrame(dct,columns=["first_name","last_name","female","age","preTestScore","postTestScore"])
print(df)
# creat scatter plot
plt.figure(figsize=(10,5))
plt.scatter(df.preTestScore, df.postTestScore, s=df.age)
plt.show()

  first_name last_name  female  age  preTestScore  postTestScore
0      Jason    Miller       0   42             4             25
1      Molly  Jacobson       1   52            24             94
2       Tina       Ali       1   36            31             57
3       Jake    Milner       0   24             2             62
4        Amy     Cooze       1   73             3             70
